                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> From the quest text, combining spells in this box isnt going to get you different spells, but spell components.  Here is the full text of the chat with the evil sage:<br /><br />[Mon Oct 21 18:52:04 2002] Sage Gunyth turns a condescending eye toward you. 'I am quite busy here, and I do not appreciate interruptions.  My [research] is important, and I do not have time to explain everything to you.'<br />[Mon Oct 21 18:52:13 2002] You say, 'tell me about your research'<br />[Mon Oct 21 18:52:13 2002] Sage Gunyth says 'Well it seems that I am not going to rid myself of you so easily so I will explain what I can.  I will be sure to use small words and simple concepts so you will be sure to understand.  Every spell is much like an orchestra; there are different instruments and octaves, and every instrument has a range of notes.  These notes are the important component. [Continue]'<br />[Mon Oct 21 18:52:25 2002] You say, 'continue'<br />[Mon Oct 21 18:52:26 2002] Sage Gunyth says 'It is my theory that all of the notes have been discovered, and creating new spells will just be a matter of combining notes in new and different fashions.  Since you seem so interested in my research, I can use assistance in gathering notes.  I have separated all the spells that are readily accessible to me, but I do not have time to gather components from the more difficult to obtain spells. [Continue]'<br />[Mon Oct 21 18:52:36 2002] You say, 'continue'<br />[Mon Oct 21 18:52:36 2002] Sage Gunyth says 'I have constructed this extractor to break spells apart into their notes.  It will not work on all spells, and I do not have time to compile a list of spells that it will and will not work on.  As my apprentice, as that seems to be what you are intent on becoming, you will separate any spells you come across and return the notes to me here, you will need to insert four spell scrolls of the same power belonging to different arcane circles.  For some reason I the extractor only works for spells between the 10th and 14th circles, I hope to have that problems resolved soon.  This extractor is not simple to use, and you will find you will have more success with the more powerful spells if you have a greater understanding on how spells are constructed.  There is one more [task] that I require of my understudy.'<br />[Mon Oct 21 18:53:14 2002] You say, 'what other task'<br />[Mon Oct 21 18:53:14 2002] Sage Gunyth says 'There are two other Sages who like to call themselves my equals.  They are taking different paths in their studies, and it would be to our benefit to have access to their work, I created that extractor with their aid so I know their methods cannot be far from my own.  You must also gather what information you can from their research and return Balic's research to Onirelin Gali my assistiant, and Xelrin's research to Xasri Virek his associate.  I have nothing more for you, and I have been distracted long enough, be off!'<br /><br />Anyway, in addition to the stuff I have already posted, I tried a bunch of different L39-51 Necromancer alteration spells, that didnt work.  I then tried 4 different types of L39 Nec spells, conj, abj, evo, alt.  That didnt work either.  You can see from the text that research skill does play a part in this, but I wasnt even getting valid combinations so mine wasnt coming into play.  I have 185 Research FWIW.  I was fairly burned out on running around all over PoK and buying up tons of old crappy spells at this point.  So I logged.  I am not one for pioneering quests I guess.<br /><br />As for other PoP stuff...<br /><br />The Erudite Necro in the library sells our sub 61 level spells, shrink companion and the poison DDs.<br /><br />I found an Iksar Warlock guildmaster on the dark side of PoK who will give you XP if you hand in your Blighted Armor...not much xp though.  I had 3 pieces of Blighted left and I gave him all of them.  I got about 1/2 a blue in 61 and 2 peridots...<br /><br />XP seems to pretty much suck in 61.  I dinged in FG.  1/2 of the shrooms and even some of the Fungus Beasts turned light blue.  I kept xp 50/50 to see how 61 was in relation to aa xp.  After 1 blue of AA xp I had around 1/5th of a blue in regular xp.<br /><br />I zoned into Plane of Nightmare.  Lot of see invis stuff right near the zone in.  I tried pulling a blood raven with epic.  Resist.  Rooted him.  Backed up to cook him and it broke and proceeded to whack me for up to 304, so I gated.<br /><br />Sayleth<br /><br /><br /><br />And I looked, and behold a pale horse: and his name that sat on him was Death - Revelation 6:8<br /><br />Edited by - Sayleth on 10/21/2002  23:06:42</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
