                      &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=87515&TOPIC_ID=10050&FORUM_ID=2"><img src="images/icon_reply_topic.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="Reply with Quote" title="Reply with Quote" align="absmiddle" hspace="6" /></a>
                      <hr noshade size="2"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> ". . . you will need to insert four spell scrolls of the same power belonging to different arcane circles. For some reason I the extractor only works for spells between the 10th and 14th circles"<br /><br />Okay power = Spell Class (i.e. Abj, Alt, Con, Div, Evo)<br />arcane circle = Spell Level (it is repeated twice in the text)<br /><br />So four spells of the same spell power from 4 seperate levels between 39 and 51.<br /><br />". . .you will separate any spells you come across"<br /><br />I agree with the earlier poster that this means dropped spells or research spells.  If you leave in all spells you have to many combinations.<br /><br />Okay so now we look at dropped/researched spells from 39 - 51.  If you look only Alteration has 4 spells that spans across 4 different levels so we will only look at Alteration spells.<br /><br />This now means if you are going to use a spell from the 10th, 11th or 13th Circle then you only have one choice: Chilling Embrace, Corporal Empathy, and Improved Invisibility Vs Undead respectively.<br /><br />Take these three spells as base spells and combine in the remaining 5 spells: Bond Of Death, Lich, Paralyzing Earth, Scarfice, Splurt to get the notes to make higher level spells.<br /><br />To take a guess I would assume that the notes you get for each spell would look something like this:<br /><br />Bond of Death = Touch of Mujaki<br />Lich = Seduction of Saryn<br />Paralyzing Earth = Petrifying Earth<br />Sacrifice = Imbue Nightmare<br />Splurt = Saryns Kiss<br /><br />If my logic is really flawed please let me know, and if you test it and it works let me know that as well.<br /><br /><br /><br />"And may thee farewell, wherever thy fare!<br />Sislibik Underfoot<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=255911" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=255911</a><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
