                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Ok progress:<br /><br />I logged and looked more closely at the spell lists.  Seeing as how each int casting class had pretty much just one level 50 spell, and it was dropped.  I decided to get them all and try those.  Combining Translocate, Improved Invis, IIvU, and Monster Summon II got me a no drop 'da note'.<br /><br />Encouraged, I tried a bunch of level 51 spells.  Atols, Splurt, ToT and Gift of Xev got me a no drop 'Eio Note'.<br /><br />I think 10th circle means L39 spells, so I didnt think any 52 spells would work, so I didnt try any.<br /><br />All classes but Mages have a dropped L39 spell from the expansions, I didnt want to try and guess which Mage spell they might want, so I didnt try any L39 combinations.<br /><br />All classes have 44th level NPC dropped spells from Velious, so that is what I tried next.  Boon of Garou, Corpal Empathy, Elemental Maelstrom and Enticement of Flame got me a 'Bep Note', again no drop.<br /><br />For 49, there are not many dropped spells (lol GDMF...), so its probably research spells they are wanting there.  I didnt mess with them though as there are a bunch and I was tired and oncall at work in the am.<br /><br />So, I found 3 of the 5.  Still need 39 amd 49 most likely.  Anyway, I went back to the evil sage and proudly handed him a bep note.  I got xp, and a lore no drop 'Amulet of Knowledge' with 5 charges of shade...woot?<br /><br />There was no text at all aside from the xp message...I then handed him the Da Note and got a lore/no drop 'Arcane Quill' with 5 charges of Elemental Armor.  Again, xp and no text at all.  Finally, handed him the Eio note and got a 'Gem of Flowing Breath' lore/no drop with 5 charges of Everlasting Breath.  Again, same deal, no quest text.  Kind of lame really.<br /><br />I speculate that these uber shitty rewards must have something to do with another quest, perhaps that of the good sage as he mentions sticking items in the box and combining them.  I tried combining the stuff I got, but no dice.<br /><br />I tried to find some words and runes to see if I could get some combines for the neutral sage, but I couldnt find very many forsale and didnt get very far with that.<br /><br />All of the combines were trivial at 185 and combining the stuff again yielded the same notes.<br /><br />Sayleth<br /><br /><br /><br />And I looked, and behold a pale horse: and his name that sat on him was Death - Revelation 6:8<br /><br />Edited by - Sayleth on 10/22/2002  01:03:10</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
